---
import LegalPage from "../../components/LegalPage.astro";

const locale = "en";
const updatedAt = "March 17, 2026";
const pageDescription =
  "This policy explains how ISAF S.A. processes personal data in connection with the use of the website and with requests sent through the contact form.";
---

<LegalPage
  locale={locale}
  currentPage="privacy"
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description={pageDescription}
  updatedAt={updatedAt}
>
  <section class="rounded-2xl border border-white/[0.08] bg-white/[0.03] p-6 sm:p-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">1. Data controller</h2>
    <div class="space-y-3 text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        The controller of personal data is <strong>ISAF S.A.</strong>, with correspondence address at
        68 Lugoj Street, P.O. Box 012212, District 1, Bucharest, Romania, registered under
        <strong> VAT No.: 473734</strong> and <strong>Trade Register No.: J40/1079/1991</strong>.
      </p>
      <p>
        For questions regarding data protection or to exercise your rights, you may contact us at
        <a href="mailto:office@isaf.ro" class="text-red-400 hover:text-red-300"> office@isaf.ro</a> or by phone at
        <a href="tel:+40212208075" class="text-red-400 hover:text-red-300"> +40 21 220 80 75</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="rounded-2xl border border-white/[0.08] bg-white/[0.03] p-6 sm:p-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">2. Data we may process</h2>
    <div class="space-y-3 text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
      <p>Depending on how you interact with the website, we may process the following categories of data:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
        <li>identification and contact data you provide directly: name, company, email address, subject, and message content;</li>
        <li>technical data commonly generated by the use of the website, such as IP address, access date and time, browser and device information, and technical logs necessary for security and service operation;</li>
        <li>website usage data collected through Google Analytics 4 only after you consent to analytics, such as page views and certain essential website interactions;</li>
        <li>any other data you choose to communicate voluntarily in later correspondence.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="rounded-2xl border border-white/[0.08] bg-white/[0.03] p-6 sm:p-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">3. Purposes and legal grounds</h2>
    <div class="space-y-3 text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
      <p>We process data only where there is a defined purpose and an applicable legal basis, especially:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
        <li>to respond to requests sent through the contact form or by email and to take pre-contractual steps at your request;</li>
        <li>to administer and secure the website, prevent abuse, investigate incidents, and protect our IT infrastructure;</li>
        <li>to measure website traffic and performance using Google Analytics 4, strictly on the basis of your consent for analytics;</li>
        <li>to comply with legal obligations applicable to us, including archiving, compliance, and cooperation with competent authorities;</li>
        <li>to establish, exercise, or defend rights in judicial or extrajudicial proceedings.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        The legal grounds we usually rely on are taking steps at the request of the data subject before entering into
        a contract, compliance with legal obligations, the controller's legitimate interest in ensuring the operation,
        security, and defense of its activity, as well as the user's consent regarding analytics through Google Analytics 4.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="rounded-2xl border border-white/[0.08] bg-white/[0.03] p-6 sm:p-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">4. Source of the data</h2>
    <div class="space-y-3 text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        As a rule, we collect data directly from you when you complete the contact form, send us an email,
        or contact us by phone.
      </p>
      <p>
        Certain technical data may be generated automatically by the hosting and security systems used for
        operating the website.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="rounded-2xl border border-white/[0.08] bg-white/[0.03] p-6 sm:p-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">5. Who may receive the data</h2>
    <div class="space-y-3 text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
      <p>Data may be accessible, on a need-to-know basis, to the following categories of recipients:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
        <li>authorized staff within ISAF S.A.;</li>
        <li>providers of hosting, IT maintenance, electronic communications, and email/SMTP services acting, where appropriate, as processors;</li>
        <li>web analytics service providers activated only after consent, such as Google Analytics 4;</li>
        <li>professional advisers, auditors, or lawyers where this is necessary;</li>
        <li>public authorities or other third parties if disclosure is required by law or necessary to defend a right.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="rounded-2xl border border-white/[0.08] bg-white/[0.03] p-6 sm:p-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">6. International transfers</h2>
    <div class="space-y-3 text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        We generally aim to use suppliers and infrastructure located in the European Union or the European Economic Area.
        If, exceptionally, certain data were to be transferred outside the EEA, such transfer would take place only
        under the conditions and safeguards permitted by applicable law, such as an adequacy decision or standard contractual clauses.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="rounded-2xl border border-white/[0.08] bg-white/[0.03] p-6 sm:p-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">7. How long we keep data</h2>
    <div class="space-y-3 text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        We retain data only for the period necessary for the purposes for which it was collected. In the case of requests
        sent through the contact form, the data is generally retained for the time required to handle the request and then
        for a reasonable professional archiving period, which usually does not exceed <strong>3 years from the last interaction</strong>,
        except where the law requires a longer period or where retention is necessary to establish, exercise, or defend a right.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="rounded-2xl border border-white/[0.08] bg-white/[0.03] p-6 sm:p-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">8. Your rights</h2>
    <div class="space-y-3 text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
      <p>Under Regulation (EU) 2016/679, you benefit from the following rights:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
        <li>the right of access to the processed data;</li>
        <li>the right to rectify inaccurate or incomplete data;</li>
        <li>the right to erasure where the legal conditions are met;</li>
        <li>the right to restriction of processing;</li>
        <li>the right to object, especially where processing is based on legitimate interest;</li>
        <li>the right to data portability, where applicable;</li>
        <li>the right not to be subject to a decision based solely on automated processing, if such processing were to be used;</li>
        <li>the right to lodge a complaint with the Romanian National Supervisory Authority for Personal Data Processing;</li>
        <li>the right to bring claims before the competent courts.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="rounded-2xl border border-white/[0.08] bg-white/[0.03] p-6 sm:p-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">9. How to exercise your rights</h2>
    <div class="space-y-3 text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        To exercise the rights mentioned above, you may send us a request at
        <a href="mailto:office@isaf.ro" class="text-red-400 hover:text-red-300"> office@isaf.ro</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        We will review each request and respond within the term provided by law. In some situations, we may ask for
        additional information to confirm the identity of the person making the request.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="rounded-2xl border border-white/[0.08] bg-white/[0.03] p-6 sm:p-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">10. Data security</h2>
    <div class="space-y-3 text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        We apply reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect data against unauthorized access,
        disclosure, alteration, loss, or accidental or unlawful destruction.
      </p>
      <p>
        However, no IT system can guarantee absolute security. For this reason, we recommend that you do not send
        sensitive information or data that is not necessary to handle your request through the form.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="rounded-2xl border border-white/[0.08] bg-white/[0.03] p-6 sm:p-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">11. Policy changes</h2>
    <div class="space-y-3 text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        We reserve the right to update this policy whenever relevant legislative, operational, or technical changes occur.
        The updated version will be published on this page together with the date of the latest revision.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</LegalPage>
